.TH "lpfc_idiag_open" 9 "lpfc_idiag_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_idiag_open \- idiag open debugfs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_idiag_open
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
The inode pointer that contains a pointer to phba.
.IP "file" 12
The file pointer to attach the file operation.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is the entry point for the debugfs open file operation. It
gets the reference to phba from the i_private field in \fIinode\fP, it then
allocates buffer for the file operation, performs the necessary PCI config
space read into the allocated buffer according to the idiag user command
setup, and then returns a pointer to buffer in the private_data field in
\fIfile\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
This function returns zero if successful. On error it will return an
negative error value.
